ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Workers who meet with customers to help them determine their short-term and long-term financial goals and provide insurance, investment services, certificates of deposits and other financial instruments. They also contact prospective customers, evaluate costs and revenue, make financial presentations and review business trends.

Concepts.definition: Workers who meet with customers to help them determine their short-term and long-term financial goals and provide insurance, investment services, certificates of deposits and other financial instruments. They also contact prospective customers, evaluate costs and revenue, make financial presentations and review business trends.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A professional who is responsible for making a child's hospital and treatment experience less scary.

Concepts.definition: A professional who is responsible for making a child's hospital and treatment experience less scary.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A professional trained to talk with people and their families about emotional or physical needs, and to find them support services.

Concepts.definition: A professionally trained person who is employed in the administration of charity, social service, and welfare. The assistance this professional provides helps disadvantaged individuals and families adjust themselves to the community. Social workers work closely with health agencies, and are often employed by the government.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A communication process between a specially trained health professional and a person concerned about the genetic risk of disease.  The person's family and personal medical history may be discussed, and counseling may lead to genetic testing.: A person trained to work in any field of physical or mental health.

Concepts.definition: The process whereby an expert in hereditary disorders provides information about risk and clinical burden of a disorder or disorders to patients or relatives in families with genetic disorders as an aid to making informed and responsible decisions about marriage, children, early diagnosis, and handling disability.
A person trained to work in any field of physical or mental health.

PermissibleValues.value: Dietician (registered with the Commission of Dietetic Registration)

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A professional trained and qualified to provide nutritional services at individual, institutional and community levels in term of assessing nutritional needs and coordinating them with medical ones, developing and implementing nutrition programs, evaluation and reporting their results, as well as to educate people on healthy eating, and diseases prevention and treatment by means of dietary modifications.

Concepts.definition: A professional trained and qualified to provide nutritional services at individual, institutional and community levels in term of assessing nutritional needs and coordinating them with medical ones, developing and implementing nutrition programs, evaluation and reporting their results, as well as to educate people on healthy eating, and diseases prevention and treatment by means of dietary modifications.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A health professional with special training in nutrition who can offer help with the choice of foods a person eats and drinks.

Concepts.definition: A health professional with special training in nutrition who can offer help with the choice of foods a person eats and drinks.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A healthcare professional who helps people recover from an illness or injury and return to daily life. Examples of rehabilitation specialists are physical therapists and occupational therapists.

Concepts.definition: A healthcare professional who helps people recover from an illness or injury and return to daily life. Examples of rehabilitation specialists are physical therapists and occupational therapists.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A person trained in pharmacy that prepares and dispenses drugs prescribed by physicians and health practitioners. The responsibilities include instructing patients on the use, hazards, interactions, and side effects of any drug dispensed.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A nurse who is involved in the treatment and observation of patients as part of a systematic investigation.
